{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"accelerator":"GPU","kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":31329,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# AI-SOCO — Atribución de Autoría de Código Fuente\nAngel Mauricio Ramírez Herrera | A01710158\nEmiliano Gomez Gonzalez | A01710711\n\nEl objetivo es identificar al autor de un fragmento de código fuente a partir de su estilo de programación. \nEl dataset AI-SOCO contiene soluciones a problemas de programación competitiva escritas por 1,000 autores distintos. \nSe comparan tres enfoques ordenados de menor a mayor complejidad: \nun baseline de conteo de caracteres con regresión logística, \nTF-IDF con KNN siguiendo el baseline reportado en el repositorio original, \ny TF-IDF con n-gramas de caracteres combinado con un clasificador más potente.\n\nEl repositorio original reporta los siguientes resultados de referencia:\n\nRandom baseline: ~0.1% de accuracy prediciendo un autor aleatorio entre los 1,000 posibles.\nCharacters Count + Logistic Regression: 29.252% en el conjunto de desarrollo.\nTF-IDF + KNN (25 vecinos, 10K features): 62.128% en desarrollo, aunque requiere varias horas para predecir el conjunto completo.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Configuración del entorno\n\nSe clona el repositorio AI-SOCO que contiene el dataset y se verifica la disponibilidad de GPU. \nPyTorch se usa únicamente para detectar el dispositivo disponible; los modelos del notebook son de scikit-learn.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import os\nimport glob\nimport string\nimport time\nimport warnings\nimport joblib\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\n\nimport tensorflow as tf\nfrom tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential, load_model\nfrom tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, BatchNormalization\nfrom tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam\nfrom tensorflow.keras.callbacks import (\n    ModelCheckpoint, EarlyStopping, ReduceLROnPlateau\n)\nfrom tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical\n\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\nfrom sklearn.metrics import (\n    accuracy_score, f1_score, precision_score,\n    recall_score, confusion_matrix\n)\n\nprint('TensorFlow:', tf.__version__)\nprint('GPU:', tf.config.list_physical_devices('GPU'))\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:06:08.333908Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:06:08.334544Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.859158Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:06:08.334512Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.858456Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"MODEL_PATH = '/kaggle/working/models/'\nos.makedirs(MODEL_PATH, exist_ok=True)\nprint(f'Model path: {MODEL_PATH}')\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.860225Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.860785Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.865518Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.860759Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.864724Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Carga del dataset\n\nEl repositorio contiene los archivos CSV con los metadatos (uid, pid) y las carpetas con los archivos de código fuente. \nSe clona una sola vez y se verifica que el directorio exista antes de volver a clonar.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"REPO_DIR = 'AI-SOCO-REPO'\nDATA_DIR = os.path.join(REPO_DIR, 'data_dir')\n\nif not os.path.exists(REPO_DIR):\n    os.system(f'git clone https://github.com/AliOsm/AI-SOCO.git {REPO_DIR}')\n\nprint('Archivos en data_dir:', os.listdir(DATA_DIR))\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.866475Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.866772Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.876405Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:06:50.866741Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.875540Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Carga de los metadatos y los códigos fuente\n\nLos archivos CSV contienen los identificadores de autor (uid) y problema (pid). \nLos códigos fuente están en carpetas separadas nombradas por pid. \nSe cargan ambos y se unen por pid para tener el código fuente junto con la etiqueta de autor.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"train_df = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'train.csv'))\ndev_df   = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'dev.csv'))\ntest_df  = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, 'unlabeled_test.csv'))\n\nprint(f'Train: {len(train_df):,}  Dev: {len(dev_df):,}  Test: {len(test_df):,}')\nprint('Autores únicos en train:', train_df['uid'].nunique())\ntrain_df.head()\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.877845Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.878054Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.939053Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.878035Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.938461Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def load_source_codes(df, base_path):\n    source_codes = {}\n    all_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(base_path, '**', '*'), recursive=True)\n    files_only = [f for f in all_files if os.path.isfile(f)]\n\n    for filepath in files_only:\n        name_without_ext = os.path.splitext(os.path.basename(filepath))[0]\n        try:\n            pid = int(name_without_ext)\n            with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore') as f:\n                source_codes[pid] = f.read()\n        except (ValueError, OSError):\n            continue\n\n    codes_df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(source_codes, orient='index', columns=['source_code'])\n    codes_df.index.name = 'pid'\n\n    cols_to_drop = [c for c in df.columns if c in ['source_code', 'source_code_x', 'source_code_y']]\n    df_clean = df.drop(columns=cols_to_drop)\n    df_merged = pd.merge(df_clean, codes_df, on='pid', how='left')\n\n    loaded = df_merged['source_code'].notna().sum()\n    print(f'{base_path.split(\"/\")[-1]}: {loaded:,} / {len(df_merged):,} códigos cargados')\n    return df_merged\n\n\ntrain_df = load_source_codes(train_df, os.path.join(os.path.abspath(REPO_DIR), 'data_dir', 'train'))\ndev_df   = load_source_codes(dev_df,   os.path.join(os.path.abspath(REPO_DIR), 'data_dir', 'dev'))\ntest_df  = load_source_codes(test_df,  os.path.join(os.path.abspath(REPO_DIR), 'data_dir', 'test'))\n\ntrain_df = train_df.dropna(subset=['source_code'])\ndev_df   = dev_df.dropna(subset=['source_code'])\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.939880Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.940187Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:07:03.562033Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:06:59.940144Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:07:03.561201Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Análisis exploratorio\n\nSe analizan seis dimensiones del dataset: distribución de ejemplos por autor, \nlongitud total del código en caracteres, número de líneas, longitud promedio de línea, \nlos autores más representados y la relación entre líneas y caracteres totales. \nLa longitud promedio de línea y el número de líneas son features implícitos del estilo de programación: \nalgunos autores tienden a escribir líneas cortas y separar la lógica, \notros escriben expresiones densas en pocas líneas. \nEstos patrones son los que los modelos intentarán capturar.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"samples_per_author = train_df['uid'].value_counts()\ntrain_df['code_length'] = train_df['source_code'].str.len()\ntrain_df['line_count']  = train_df['source_code'].str.count('\\n')\ntrain_df['avg_line_len'] = train_df['code_length'] / (train_df['line_count'] + 1)\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(16, 9))\n\n# 1. Ejemplos por autor\naxes[0,0].hist(samples_per_author.values, bins=30, color='steelblue', edgecolor='white')\naxes[0,0].set_title('Ejemplos por autor')\naxes[0,0].set_xlabel('Número de ejemplos')\naxes[0,0].set_ylabel('Autores')\n\n# 2. Longitud de código\naxes[0,1].hist(train_df['code_length'].clip(upper=5000), bins=50,\n               color='steelblue', edgecolor='white')\naxes[0,1].set_title('Longitud del código (chars, truncada a 5000)')\naxes[0,1].set_xlabel('Caracteres')\n\n# 3. Número de líneas\naxes[0,2].hist(train_df['line_count'].clip(upper=200), bins=50,\n               color='steelblue', edgecolor='white')\naxes[0,2].set_title('Número de líneas (truncado a 200)')\naxes[0,2].set_xlabel('Líneas')\n\n# 4. Longitud promedio de línea\naxes[1,0].hist(train_df['avg_line_len'].clip(upper=100), bins=50,\n               color='steelblue', edgecolor='white')\naxes[1,0].set_title('Longitud promedio de línea')\naxes[1,0].set_xlabel('Chars / línea')\n\n# 5. Top 20 autores con más ejemplos\ntop20 = samples_per_author.head(20)\naxes[1,1].barh(top20.index.astype(str), top20.values, color='steelblue')\naxes[1,1].set_title('Top 20 autores con más ejemplos')\naxes[1,1].set_xlabel('Ejemplos')\naxes[1,1].invert_yaxis()\n\n# 6. Longitud de código vs número de líneas (muestra)\nsample = train_df.sample(2000, random_state=42)\naxes[1,2].scatter(sample['line_count'].clip(upper=200),\n                  sample['code_length'].clip(upper=5000),\n                  alpha=0.3, s=5, color='steelblue')\naxes[1,2].set_title('Líneas vs longitud total (muestra 2k)')\naxes[1,2].set_xlabel('Líneas')\naxes[1,2].set_ylabel('Caracteres')\n\nplt.suptitle('Análisis exploratorio — AI-SOCO', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n\nprint(f'Ejemplos por autor — media: {samples_per_author.mean():.1f}  '\n      f'min: {samples_per_author.min()}  max: {samples_per_author.max()}')\nprint(f'Longitud — media: {train_df[\"code_length\"].mean():.0f}  '\n      f'mediana: {train_df[\"code_length\"].median():.0f} chars')\nprint(f'Líneas   — media: {train_df[\"line_count\"].mean():.1f}  '\n      f'mediana: {train_df[\"line_count\"].median():.0f}')\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:07:03.563835Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:07:03.564458Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.915335Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:07:03.564432Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.914428Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Guardado, carga de modelos y evaluación\n\nLos modelos de Keras usan los mismos callbacks que en el repositorio SongTextClassifier: \nModelCheckpoint guarda el mejor modelo según val_loss, EarlyStopping detiene el entrenamiento \nsi no hay mejora y ReduceLROnPlateau reduce el learning rate cuando el modelo se estanca. \nSi el archivo del modelo ya existe en disco se carga directamente sin reentrenar, \npermitiendo retomar el trabajo entre sesiones.\n\nLos vectorizadores TF-IDF se guardan con joblib porque no son modelos de Keras. \nSe ajustan solo sobre el conjunto de entrenamiento para evitar filtrar información del dev al modelo.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"results = {}\n\ndef get_callbacks(model_name):\n    return [\n        ModelCheckpoint(\n            filepath=MODEL_PATH + f'{model_name}.keras',\n            monitor='val_loss',\n            save_best_only=True,\n            mode='min',\n            verbose=1\n        ),\n        EarlyStopping(\n            monitor='val_loss',\n            patience=5,\n            restore_best_weights=True,\n            verbose=1\n        ),\n        ReduceLROnPlateau(\n            monitor='val_loss',\n            factor=0.5,\n            patience=3,\n            min_lr=1e-7,\n            verbose=1\n        )\n    ]\n\n\ndef load_keras_if_exists(model_name):\n    path = MODEL_PATH + f'{model_name}.keras'\n    if os.path.exists(path):\n        print(f'Modelo cargado desde disco: {model_name}')\n        return load_model(path)\n    return None\n\n\ndef save_vectorizer(name, vec):\n    joblib.dump(vec, MODEL_PATH + f'{name}_vectorizer.joblib')\n    print(f'Vectorizador guardado: {name}_vectorizer.joblib')\n\n\ndef load_vectorizer_if_exists(name):\n    path = MODEL_PATH + f'{name}_vectorizer.joblib'\n    if os.path.exists(path):\n        print(f'Vectorizador cargado: {name}_vectorizer.joblib')\n        return joblib.load(path)\n    return None\n\n\ndef evaluate(name, y_true, y_pred, training_time=None):\n    acc       = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)\n    f1_macro  = f1_score(y_true, y_pred, average='macro',    zero_division=0)\n    f1_weight = f1_score(y_true, y_pred, average='weighted', zero_division=0)\n    prec      = precision_score(y_true, y_pred, average='macro', zero_division=0)\n    rec       = recall_score(y_true, y_pred, average='macro',    zero_division=0)\n    results[name] = {\n        'Accuracy':    round(acc,       4),\n        'F1 Macro':    round(f1_macro,  4),\n        'F1 Weighted': round(f1_weight, 4),\n        'Precision':   round(prec,      4),\n        'Recall':      round(rec,       4),\n        'Time(s)':     round(training_time, 2) if training_time else None\n    }\n    print(f'\\n{\"=\"*55}\\n  {name}\\n{\"=\"*55}')\n    print(f'  Accuracy:    {acc:.4f}  ({acc*100:.2f}%)')\n    print(f'  F1 Macro:    {f1_macro:.4f}')\n    print(f'  F1 Weighted: {f1_weight:.4f}')\n    print(f'  Precision:   {prec:.4f}')\n    print(f'  Recall:      {rec:.4f}')\n    if training_time:\n        print(f'  Tiempo:      {training_time:.2f}s')\n    return acc\n\n\ndef plot_full_cm(name, y_true, y_pred):\n    labels = sorted(set(y_true))\n    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, labels=labels)\n    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n    plt.imshow(cm, aspect='auto', cmap='Blues', interpolation='nearest')\n    plt.colorbar(label='Predicciones')\n    plt.title(f'Matriz de confusión completa ({len(labels)} autores) — {name}')\n    plt.xlabel('Predicción (uid)')\n    plt.ylabel('Real (uid)')\n    plt.tight_layout()\n    plt.show()\n    diag     = np.diag(cm)\n    row_sums = cm.sum(axis=1)\n    pca      = np.where(row_sums > 0, diag / row_sums, 0)\n    print(f'  Autores con acc = 1.0:  {(pca == 1.0).sum()}')\n    print(f'  Autores con acc = 0.0:  {(pca == 0.0).sum()}')\n    print(f'  Accuracy media por clase: {pca.mean():.4f}')\n\n\ndef plot_per_class_acc_hist(name, y_true, y_pred):\n    labels   = sorted(set(y_true))\n    cm       = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, labels=labels)\n    diag     = np.diag(cm)\n    row_sums = cm.sum(axis=1)\n    pca      = np.where(row_sums > 0, diag / row_sums, 0)\n    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 4))\n    plt.hist(pca, bins=20, color='steelblue', edgecolor='white')\n    plt.axvline(pca.mean(), color='#e74c3c', linestyle='--',\n                label=f'Media: {pca.mean():.3f}')\n    plt.title(f'Distribución de accuracy por autor — {name}')\n    plt.xlabel('Accuracy individual del autor')\n    plt.ylabel('Número de autores')\n    plt.legend()\n    plt.tight_layout()\n    plt.show()\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.916361Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.917179Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.930033Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.917154Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.929098Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Modelo base — Characters Count + MLP\n\nEl baseline del repositorio usa conteo de caracteres con regresión logística. \nAquí se reemplaza el clasificador por una red neuronal densa que corre en GPU. \nLa vectorización es idéntica: un vector de 100 dimensiones con la frecuencia de cada carácter ASCII imprimible. \nLa red aprende combinaciones no lineales de esas frecuencias, \nlo que permite capturar patrones de estilo más sutiles que la combinación lineal de la regresión logística. \nEl repositorio reporta 29.252% de accuracy con Characters+LR, \nlo que sirve como piso de referencia para este modelo.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"PRINTABLE = list(string.printable)\n\ndef char_count_vectorize(texts):\n    matrix = np.zeros((len(texts), len(PRINTABLE)), dtype=np.float32)\n    for i, text in enumerate(texts):\n        for j, ch in enumerate(PRINTABLE):\n            matrix[i, j] = text.count(ch)\n    return matrix\n\n\nle = LabelEncoder()\nle.fit(train_df['uid'])\ny_train    = le.transform(train_df['uid'])\ny_dev      = le.transform(dev_df['uid'])\nnum_classes = len(le.classes_)\n\nX_train_chars = char_count_vectorize(train_df['source_code'].tolist())\nX_dev_chars   = char_count_vectorize(dev_df['source_code'].tolist())\n\nmodel_chars = load_keras_if_exists('chars_mlp')\n\nif model_chars is None:\n    model_chars = Sequential([\n        Dense(256, activation='relu', input_shape=(len(PRINTABLE),)),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.4),\n        Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.3),\n        Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')\n    ], name='chars_mlp')\n    model_chars.compile(\n        optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=1e-3),\n        loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n        metrics=['accuracy']\n    )\n    model_chars.summary()\n    t0 = time.time()\n    model_chars.fit(\n        X_train_chars, y_train,\n        validation_data=(X_dev_chars, y_dev),\n        epochs=30,\n        batch_size=256,\n        callbacks=get_callbacks('chars_mlp'),\n        verbose=1\n    )\n    t1 = time.time()\nelse:\n    t0 = t1 = time.time()\n\ny_pred_chars = le.inverse_transform(\n    np.argmax(model_chars.predict(X_dev_chars, verbose=0), axis=1)\n)\ny_dev_labels = le.inverse_transform(y_dev)\n\nevaluate('Characters + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_chars,\n         t1 - t0 if t1 > t0 else None)\nplot_full_cm('Characters + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_chars)\nplot_per_class_acc_hist('Characters + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_chars)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.931084Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.931437Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:07:50.246954Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:07:04.931407Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:07:50.246306Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Modelo 2 — TF-IDF + MLP\n\nEl segundo baseline del repositorio usa TF-IDF con KNN. \nKNN no corre en GPU porque necesita comparar cada ejemplo contra todo el conjunto de entrenamiento en CPU. \nSe reemplaza por una red neuronal densa que opera sobre los mismos vectores TF-IDF. \nLa entrada es dispersa, por lo que se convierte a denso antes de pasar a las capas. \nLa mayor capacidad de la red respecto al modelo base permite capturar interacciones \nmás complejas entre los términos del código. \nEl repositorio reporta 62.128% de accuracy con TF-IDF+KNN como punto de referencia.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"tfidf_w = load_vectorizer_if_exists('tfidf_word')\n\nif tfidf_w is None:\n    tfidf_w = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=10000)\n    X_train_tfidf = tfidf_w.fit_transform(train_df['source_code'].astype(str))\n    save_vectorizer('tfidf_word', tfidf_w)\nelse:\n    X_train_tfidf = tfidf_w.transform(train_df['source_code'].astype(str))\n\nX_dev_tfidf = tfidf_w.transform(dev_df['source_code'].astype(str))\n\n# Convertir a denso en batches para no saturar RAM\nBATCH = 5000\n\ndef sparse_to_dense_batched(X):\n    parts = []\n    for start in range(0, X.shape[0], BATCH):\n        parts.append(X[start:start+BATCH].toarray().astype(np.float32))\n    return np.vstack(parts)\n\n\nX_train_tfidf_d = sparse_to_dense_batched(X_train_tfidf)\nX_dev_tfidf_d   = sparse_to_dense_batched(X_dev_tfidf)\nprint(f'Train: {X_train_tfidf_d.shape}  Dev: {X_dev_tfidf_d.shape}')\n\nmodel_tfidf = load_keras_if_exists('tfidf_mlp')\n\nif model_tfidf is None:\n    model_tfidf = Sequential([\n        Dense(512, activation='relu', input_shape=(X_train_tfidf_d.shape[1],)),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.4),\n        Dense(256, activation='relu'),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.3),\n        Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n        Dropout(0.2),\n        Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')\n    ], name='tfidf_mlp')\n    model_tfidf.compile(\n        optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=1e-3),\n        loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n        metrics=['accuracy']\n    )\n    model_tfidf.summary()\n    t0 = time.time()\n    model_tfidf.fit(\n        X_train_tfidf_d, y_train,\n        validation_data=(X_dev_tfidf_d, y_dev),\n        epochs=30,\n        batch_size=256,\n        callbacks=get_callbacks('tfidf_mlp'),\n        verbose=1\n    )\n    t1 = time.time()\nelse:\n    t0 = t1 = time.time()\n\ny_pred_tfidf = le.inverse_transform(\n    np.argmax(model_tfidf.predict(X_dev_tfidf_d, verbose=0), axis=1)\n)\n\nevaluate('TF-IDF + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_tfidf,\n         t1 - t0 if t1 > t0 else None)\nplot_full_cm('TF-IDF + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_tfidf)\nplot_per_class_acc_hist('TF-IDF + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_tfidf)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:07:50.248017Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:07:50.248448Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:09:11.135286Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:07:50.248413Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:09:11.134728Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Modelo 3 — TF-IDF n-gramas de caracteres + MLP profunda\n\nEste modelo combina la vectorización con n-gramas de caracteres, \nque captura patrones de formato y estilo más finos que los tokens de palabras, \ncon la arquitectura de red más profunda del conjunto. \nSe reduce max_features a 20,000 (en lugar de 50,000) para que la matriz densa \nquepa en la RAM disponible en Kaggle. Con 50,000 features la conversión a denso \nconsume más de 13 GB solo para los datos de entrenamiento, lo que causa el kernel restart. \n20,000 features mantiene la ventaja de los n-gramas de caracteres sin saturar la memoria.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"tfidf_c = load_vectorizer_if_exists('tfidf_char')\n\nif tfidf_c is None:\n    tfidf_c = TfidfVectorizer(\n        analyzer='char',\n        ngram_range=(2, 4),\n        max_features=20000,   # reducido de 50k para evitar OOM\n        sublinear_tf=True\n    )\n    X_train_char = tfidf_c.fit_transform(train_df['source_code'].astype(str))\n    save_vectorizer('tfidf_char', tfidf_c)\nelse:\n    X_train_char = tfidf_c.transform(train_df['source_code'].astype(str))\n\nX_dev_char = tfidf_c.transform(dev_df['source_code'].astype(str))\n\nX_train_char_d = sparse_to_dense_batched(X_train_char)\nX_dev_char_d   = sparse_to_dense_batched(X_dev_char)\nprint(f'Train: {X_train_char_d.shape}  Dev: {X_dev_char_d.shape}')\n\nmodel_char = load_keras_if_exists('char_mlp')\n\nif model_char is None:\n    model_char = Sequential([\n        Dense(512, activation='relu', input_shape=(X_train_char_d.shape[1],)),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.5),\n        Dense(256, activation='relu'),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.4),\n        Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.3),\n        Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')\n    ], name='char_mlp')\n    model_char.compile(\n        optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=5e-4),\n        loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n        metrics=['accuracy']\n    )\n    model_char.summary()\n    t0 = time.time()\n    model_char.fit(\n        X_train_char_d, y_train,\n        validation_data=(X_dev_char_d, y_dev),\n        epochs=30,\n        batch_size=256,\n        callbacks=get_callbacks('char_mlp'),\n        verbose=1\n    )\n    t1 = time.time()\nelse:\n    t0 = t1 = time.time()\n\ny_pred_char = le.inverse_transform(\n    np.argmax(model_char.predict(X_dev_char_d, verbose=0), axis=1)\n)\n\nevaluate('TF-IDF char n-gramas + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_char,\n         t1 - t0 if t1 > t0 else None)\nplot_full_cm('TF-IDF char n-gramas + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_char)\nplot_per_class_acc_hist('TF-IDF char n-gramas + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_char)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:09:11.137141Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:09:11.137472Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.646553Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:09:11.137449Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.645736Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print('Modelos guardados:')\nfor f in sorted(os.listdir(MODEL_PATH)):\n    size = os.path.getsize(os.path.join(MODEL_PATH, f)) / (1024*1024)\n    print(f'  {f}  ({size:.1f} MB)')\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.647500Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.647855Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.653144Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.647817Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.652549Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Comparación de modelos\n\nSe comparan los tres modelos junto con los baselines reportados en el repositorio original. \nLos valores de referencia son: random baseline ~0.1%, Characters+LR 29.252%, TF-IDF+KNN 62.128%.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"baselines = {\n    'Random (referencia)':        {'Accuracy': 0.0010, 'F1 Macro': None, 'F1 Weighted': None, 'Precision': None, 'Recall': None, 'Time(s)': None},\n    'Characters+LR (referencia)': {'Accuracy': 0.2925, 'F1 Macro': None, 'F1 Weighted': None, 'Precision': None, 'Recall': None, 'Time(s)': None},\n    'TF-IDF+KNN (referencia)':    {'Accuracy': 0.6213, 'F1 Macro': None, 'F1 Weighted': None, 'Precision': None, 'Recall': None, 'Time(s)': None},\n}\nall_results = {**baselines, **results}\n\ndf_res = pd.DataFrame(all_results).T.reset_index()\ndf_res.columns = ['Modelo', 'Accuracy', 'F1 Macro', 'F1 Weighted', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Time(s)']\ndf_res['Accuracy'] = df_res['Accuracy'].astype(float)\ndf_res = df_res.sort_values('Accuracy', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\n\nprint('='*75)\nprint('COMPARATIVA — AI-SOCO Authorship Attribution')\nprint('='*75)\nprint(df_res[['Modelo','Accuracy','F1 Macro','Precision','Recall','Time(s)']].to_string(index=False))\nprint('='*75)\n\n# Barras por métrica\nmetrics = ['Accuracy', 'F1 Macro', 'Precision', 'Recall']\ndf_plot = df_res.dropna(subset=['F1 Macro'])  # excluir referencias sin F1\ndf_ref  = df_res[df_res['F1 Macro'].isna()]\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(18, 5))\ncolors = plt.cm.tab10(np.linspace(0, 1, len(df_plot)))\n\nfor ax, metric in zip(axes, metrics):\n    vals = df_plot[metric].astype(float)\n    bars = ax.barh(df_plot['Modelo'], vals, color=colors)\n    ax.set_title(metric)\n    ax.set_xlim(0, 1.0)\n    ax.invert_yaxis()\n    # Líneas de referencia de accuracy del repo\n    if metric == 'Accuracy':\n        ax.axvline(0.6213, color='#e74c3c', linestyle='--', linewidth=1,\n                   label='TF-IDF+KNN ref (62.13%)')\n        ax.axvline(0.2925, color='#e67e22', linestyle='--', linewidth=1,\n                   label='Chars+LR ref (29.25%)')\n        ax.legend(fontsize=7)\n    for bar, v in zip(bars, vals):\n        ax.text(v + 0.01, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,\n                f'{v:.3f}', va='center', fontsize=8)\n\nplt.suptitle('Comparación de modelos — AI-SOCO', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.654192Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.654526Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-29T06:14:07.038288Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-29T06:14:06.654457Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-29T06:14:07.037407Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Accuracy por número de ejemplos de entrenamiento por autor\n\nSe analiza si los modelos funcionan mejor para autores con más ejemplos en el conjunto de entrenamiento. \nEsto permite entender las limitaciones reales del sistema: \nsi la accuracy cae mucho para autores con pocos ejemplos, \nel modelo no generalizará bien a autores poco representados.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"author_counts = train_df['uid'].value_counts()\n\ndef accuracy_by_group(y_true, y_pred, author_counts, bins=[0,5,10,20,50,10000]):\n    df = pd.DataFrame({'uid': y_true, 'pred': y_pred})\n    df['n_train'] = df['uid'].map(author_counts)\n    df['correct'] = df['uid'] == df['pred']\n    df['group']   = pd.cut(df['n_train'], bins=bins,\n                           labels=[f'{bins[i]+1}-{bins[i+1]}' for i in range(len(bins)-1)])\n    return df.groupby('group', observed=True)['correct'].mean()\n\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\nfor name, y_pred in [\n    ('Characters+MLP',          y_pred_chars),\n    ('TF-IDF+MLP',              y_pred_tfidf),\n    ('TF-IDF char ngram+MLP',   y_pred_char),\n]:\n    acc_by_group = accuracy_by_group(y_dev_labels, y_pred, author_counts)\n    ax.plot(acc_by_group.index, acc_by_group.values, marker='o', label=name)\n\nax.set_title('Accuracy por número de ejemplos de entrenamiento por autor')\nax.set_xlabel('Ejemplos de entrenamiento por autor')\nax.set_ylabel('Accuracy')\nax.legend()\nax.grid(True, alpha=0.4)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"